cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DS

This paper introduces a logic for specifying software architectures with quantitative features, which suggests it could belong to the categories of logic (cs.LO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, since the paper focuses on the development of a logic and its efficient construction, it is most likely to belong to the category of logic (cs.LO). The other categories are still possible because the paper deals with software architectures and quantitative features, but they are less likely given the emphasis on logic.
